The paper focuses on improving the robustness of deep neural networks against adversarial attacks in computer vision tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method involves integrating a regularization term into the classification objective, which involves optimizing potential perturbations and punishing them by a large margin in an iterative way. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the security aspect of deep learning, which suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on deep face recognition, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
